text: Location of Medzilaborce District in the Prešov Region. Oľšinkov is a village and municipality in the Medzilaborce District in the Prešov Region of far north-eastern Slovakia. ==History== In historical records the village was first mentioned in 1567. ==Geography== The municipality lies at an altitude of 450 metres and covers an area of 7.652 km². It has a population of about 30 people. ==External links== *http://www.statistics.sk/mosmis/eng/run.html Category:Villages and municipalities in Medzilaborce District
